peopleAlsoAsk.question: How do I find the value of my classic car?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Classic car values are determined by a multitude of factors both in and out of the owner's control. A collector car's market value is best determined by understanding supply and demand, using historical sale prices, and reviewing current asking prices on available inventory.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: How much does it cost to appraise a classic car?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: In general, a good vehicle appraisal will cost somewhere between $250 and $750, although the cost can be higher for custom and modified automobiles. In such cases, higher prices reflect the time and attention to detail required to properly research and document a custom-built vehicle.
